    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house in Toronto, is essentially a secure holding place for funds and documents until the sale is finalized. Think of it like a highly regulated, neutral third party—the escrow agent—who holds your deposit and the seller's proceeds. It's a crucial step to ensure that both you and the seller fulfill your obligations before the keys are handed over. Without it, it's a risky transaction, and the escrow agent acts as the reliable middleman, preventing any one party from being tricked or having their money vanish.",
