    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so like, who actually holds the money? is it the bank or a lawyer or something? i just wanna make sure it's safe and won't just disappear during the process.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money is typically held by a licensed real estate lawyer or a specialized title company acting as the escrow agent. These professionals are bound by strict legal regulations, which is why their involvement is so vital. They are essentially the gatekeepers, ensuring that the funds are only released once all the contractual conditions—like the satisfactory inspection or title search—have been met. You can trust them because they are legally accountable for safeguarding those funds.",
